bodyenglish:
Studio XX is pleased to host artist Kimura Byol with PROJECT #6261 MONTR&Eacute;AL, from August 25th to October 9th, 2016, as part of our 2016-17 residency program.&nbsp;




During the Studio XX artist residency (August 25th to October 9th), kimura byol-nathalie lemoine will make a non-linear narrative and interactive film (Korsakow).&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&quot;With this residency at Studio XX, I will explore the possibilities of non-linear narrative and interactive film with the software Korsakow as a playful and participative web-documentary.

This project incorporates the particular reality of Montreal&rsquo;s local street address system, which differs from other realities which are familiar to me, such as those of Belgium where I was adopted and South Korea where I was born. I had the idea to use my adoption number (#6261) to get to know the new city (where I wanted to immigrate) through meeting with the inhabitants of that street number.

I gave myself a structure of 100 days to work from this concept.I randomly chose 100 streets and sent a call to participation to those selected addresses. &nbsp;I visited the city by foot and public transportation, carrying only my camera to conform/inform the existence of the number #6261and to document the investigation process and meetings.

I had the privilege of discovering different social, ethnic, economic and linguistic realities.&quot;

&nbsp;

Illustration : Eloisa Aquino

Caroline Alexander and Cynthia Hammond

Saturday, October 22, 2PM to 4 PM @ STUDIO XX&nbsp; 

What are the personal, spatial, and performative strategies of finding safety in the city? In two workshops, participants create &ldquo;memory maps&rdquo;: subjective drawings based on personal experience and spatial memory. These maps visualize the embodied knowledge of gendered urban risk and safety, and will be exhibited in spring 2017.




Safety Strategies is a collaborative art project that seeks to critically explore and creatively document how women and self-identified women, trans, members of the LGBTQ community, and women with limited mobility build a sense of safety when negotiating Montreal&rsquo;s urban environments. While cities are often poorly designed and potentially dangerous, they are not unalterable. Spatial Strategies foregrounds the ways in which users negotiate and challenge the gendered dangers of cities.

&nbsp;

The collaborative production of the exhibition will take the form of two workshops in the fall of 2016: one at Studio XX, and the other at a wheelchair-accessible space at Concordia University. Participants will be invited to think about times when they have had to negotiate a specific urban location or itinerary in which they felt at risk. We will then ask participants to create &ldquo;memory maps&rdquo; that visualize this embodied knowledge. Memory maps, introduced to us through the practice of artist Marlene Creates, http://www.marlenecreates.ca/, are subjective drawings based on personal experience and spatial memory. The maps will be the locus for a group discussion, and in personal, written reflections. These outcomes will be the basis of the exhibition.

&nbsp;

As an exhibition, Safety Strategies will include the memory maps and written reflections. The installation will also include a drawing station where visitors can add to the collection of stories, maps, and strategies.

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

REQUIREMENTS

No previous technical knowledge required.

&nbsp;

PRACTICAL INFORMATION

20 participants maximum per workshop

The main language of the preliminary presentations will be English, but questions and discussion in French and English will be warmly encouraged.

Information | Registration : ateliers@studioxx.org &nbsp;

&nbsp;

bodyfrench:
DATE LIMITE : 20 OCTOBRE 2016

&nbsp;

L&rsquo;histoire contemporaine se caract&eacute;rise par des exp&eacute;riences de d&eacute;localisation (dislocation). Dans le contexte de la mondialisation, le capital, la culture, les biens, l&rsquo;information et les personnes se d&eacute;placent d&rsquo;un endroit &agrave; un autre. Les gens voyagent m&eacute;taphoriquement et g&eacute;ographiquement pour diverses raisons : par plaisir, par n&eacute;cessit&eacute;, &agrave; cause des guerres ou des politiques nationales et internationales, ainsi que des catastrophes naturelles. En adoptant le sens g&eacute;n&eacute;ral du terme d&eacute;localisation (dislocation) - &agrave; savoir &ecirc;tre &ldquo;hors de propos&rdquo; ou &ldquo;&ecirc;tre en dehors de&rdquo; &agrave; partir d&#39;un endroit premier, d&rsquo;un lieu, d&rsquo;une position ou d&rsquo;un &eacute;tat - le Studio XX accueille des propositions qui explorent des formes mat&eacute;rielles et m&eacute;taphoriques de d&eacute;localisation (dislocation) de mani&egrave;re ludique, critique et hypoth&eacute;tique.

Dans le cadre des c&eacute;l&eacute;brations pour le 375e anniversaire de la ville de Montr&eacute;al en 2017, nous encourageons des propositions qui interrogent comment cet espace g&eacute;ographique et physique - l&#39;&icirc;le de Montr&eacute;al en tant que territoire non c&eacute;d&eacute; - &nbsp;est-il un site d&rsquo;exp&eacute;riences et d&rsquo;histoires diff&eacute;rentes ? Comment peut-il simultan&eacute;ment inspirer un sentiment d&rsquo;appartenance pour certaines personnes et peut &ecirc;tre ressenti comme hostile et dangereux pour d&rsquo;autres ? Nous accueillons &eacute;galement des propositions qui r&eacute;fl&eacute;chissent au r&ocirc;le des m&eacute;dias et des technologies (c&rsquo;est-&agrave;-dire les t&eacute;l&eacute;phones mobiles, les v&eacute;hicules a&eacute;riens sans pilote ayant des capacit&eacute;s mortelles) dans la red&eacute;finition des notions de lieu, de d&eacute;localisation (dislocation) et de pr&eacute;sence.

&nbsp;

LES TH&Eacute;MATIQUES PEUVENT COMPRENDRE :


	les d&eacute;bats f&eacute;ministes autour des questions de l&#39;emplacement et de d&eacute;localisation (dislocation);
	les r&eacute;cits introspectifs et autobiographiques sur l&#39;appartenance ou la non appartenance;
	les r&eacute;f&eacute;rences aux fronti&egrave;res, aux d&eacute;placements et &agrave; la mobilit&eacute;;
	les r&eacute;flexions critiques sur la notion &ldquo;d&rsquo;&ecirc;tre hors de propos&rdquo; en lien avec la th&eacute;matique des colons blancs europ&eacute;ens au Canada et/ou &agrave; Montr&eacute;al;
	la d&eacute;localisation (dislocation) en tant que critique face aux diff&eacute;rentes appartenances, identit&eacute;s et aux discours sur les origines fig&eacute;es;
	les r&eacute;f&eacute;rences aux connotations n&eacute;gatives du d&eacute;placement g&eacute;ographique : d&eacute;portation, expulsion, &ecirc;tre chass&eacute;-e d&rsquo;un endroit;
	les &eacute;tudes sur les processus par lesquels l&#39;identit&eacute; se cr&eacute;e en relation avec des emplacements physiques ou des d&eacute;localisations (dislocations);
	les relations d&rsquo;amour/haine avec les technologies localis&eacute;es;
	l&#39;angoisse d&#39;&ecirc;tre en dehors des m&eacute;dias sociaux;
	le r&ocirc;le des nouveaux m&eacute;dias et des technologies dans la cr&eacute;ation de souvenirs, de sentiments d&rsquo;appartenance et d&#39;identit&eacute;;
	la d&eacute;localisation (dislocation) en tant qu&rsquo;exp&eacute;rience commune pour les corps non-h&eacute;t&eacute;ronormatifs ou &ldquo;capables&rdquo; dans les espaces concrets et en ligne;
	les red&eacute;finitions de la notion de pr&eacute;sence ; l&#39;id&eacute;e d&#39;&ecirc;tre pr&eacute;sent-e par rapport au r&ocirc;le des technologies immersives et de r&eacute;alit&eacute; augment&eacute;e (cf. Pokemon Go).



&nbsp;

CE QUE NOUS RECHERCHONS

Les participant-e-s peuvent pr&eacute;senter des propositions pour des expositions, des ateliers ou des &eacute;v&eacute;nements/activit&eacute;s d&rsquo;une journ&eacute;e.

Exemples de projets pour les expositions : net art, art &eacute;lectronique et audio, oeuvre interactive, art radiophonique, art vid&eacute;o, installation, m&eacute;dias g&eacute;olocalis&eacute;s, art du jeu vid&eacute;o, r&eacute;alit&eacute; augment&eacute;e, bio art, interventions publiques, pratiques du libre et ancr&eacute;es dans la communaut&eacute;.

Exemples d&rsquo;&eacute;v&eacute;nement/activit&eacute; d&rsquo;une journ&eacute;e : conversation, table ronde, discussion, performance.

Nous recherchons des propositions inspir&eacute;es par (mais sans s&#39;y limiter) : les f&eacute;minismes, les &eacute;tudes critiques sur la race, le cyberf&eacute;minisme, les &eacute;tudes queer et les &eacute;tudes relatives aux personnes handicap&eacute;es.

Les soumissions sont accept&eacute;es en fran&ccedil;ais ou en anglais.

Le Studio XX accueille des projets d&rsquo;artistes s&rsquo;identifiant comme femmes et/ou issu-e-s de communaut&eacute;s s&rsquo;inscrivant dans une diversit&eacute; des genres, de commissaires et d&rsquo;activistes, ainsi que de collectifs et d&rsquo;organisations.


&nbsp;

CE QUE NOUS OFFRONS

Le Studio XX offre des cachets d&rsquo;artistes bas&eacute;s sur la grille des bar&egrave;mes de diffusion en arts m&eacute;diatiques du CQAM.

Les projets retenus b&eacute;n&eacute;ficient d&rsquo;un soutien artistique et technique (*&agrave; d&eacute;finir en fonction de chaque projet et selon les ressources disponibles).

* Veuillez prendre note que cet appel ne concerne pas des projets qui n&eacute;cessitent un soutien &agrave; la production (les oeuvres soumises doivent avoir atteint leur stade de diffusion).

Avant de soumettre une proposition, les candidat-e-s sont fortement encourag&eacute;-e-s &agrave; consulter le mandat du Studio XX, les modalit&eacute;s de soumission et les plans de la galerie.

&nbsp;

MODALIT&Eacute;S DE SOUMISSION

Pour soumettre une proposition au Studio XX, veuillez envoyer le dossier de candidature sous un format .pdf ou dans un fichier .zip (taille du fichier max. 5 MB) &agrave; programmation @ studioxx.org au plus tard le 20 octobre 2016, &agrave; minuit.

S&rsquo;il vous pla&icirc;t, veuillez t&eacute;l&eacute;charger et compl&eacute;ter le FORMULAIRE et inclure les documents requis.

Objet du courriel : Propositions - Programmation 2017-2018
Date limite de soumission : 20 octobre 2016

Seules les soumissions compl&egrave;tes seront prises en consid&eacute;ration. Les participant-e-s recevront un accus&eacute; de r&eacute;ception. Les participant-e-s s&eacute;lectionn&eacute;-e-s seront avis&eacute;-e-s en janvier 2017.

Pour toute autre question et demande de renseignements, contactez-nous &agrave; : info @ studioxx.org

bodyenglish:
DEADLINE : OCTOBER 20TH 2016

&nbsp;

Experiences of dislocation typify the contemporary moment. In the context of globalization, capital, culture, goods, information, and people move from one place to another. Subjects travel metaphorically and geographically for various reasons: for leisure or necessity, and because of wars, international and national policies, and natural disasters. Taking the general meaning of dislocation as being &ldquo;out of place&rdquo; from or&nbsp;&ldquo;being outside&rdquo; of a primary location, position, or state, Studio XX welcomes proposals that explore material and metaphorical forms of dislocation in playful, critical, and speculative ways.

In the context of the celebrations being held for &nbsp;Montr&eacute;al&#39;s 375th anniversary in 2017, we invite proposals that investigate how the geographical and physical space of Montreal as an unceded territory is the site of different experiences and stories. Interpreted in this way, it can inspire a sense of home for some people, while simultaneously inspiring a sense of hostility and threat/unease for others. We especially welcome proposals that reflect on the role of media and technology (i.e. mobile phones, unmanned aerial vehicles with deadly capacities) in redefining the notions of location, dislocation, and presence. &nbsp;

&nbsp;

TOPICS MIGHT INCLUDE&nbsp;:


	feminist debates around a politics of location and dislocation;
	self-reflective, autobiographical accounts on belonging or not belonging;
	explorations of &nbsp;borders, displacements, and mobility;
	critical insights into the notion of &ldquo;being out of place&rdquo; in relation to white European settlers in Canada and/or Montreal;
	dislocation as a critique of &nbsp;various homes, identities and discourses of fixed origins;
	references to negative connotations of geographical displacement: deportation, expulsion, being thrown out of a place;
	processes through which identity comes into being in relation to physical locations or dislocations;
	love/hate relationships with locative technologies;
	the anxiety of &ldquo;being out of place&rdquo; in social media;
	new media and technologies&#39; role in creating memories, senses of belonging and identity;
	dislocation as a common experience for non-heteronormative or &ldquo;able&rdquo; bodies in tangible buildings as well as online;
	redefinitions of the notion of presence; for instance, the idea of being present in relation to role of immersive and augmented reality technologies (i.e. Pokemon Go).



&nbsp;

WHAT WE ARE LOOKING FOR

Participants may present proposals for Exhibitions, Workshops, or a One-day Event/Activity

Examples of proposals for exhibitions: net art, audio and electronic art, interactive pieces, radio art, video art, installation, locative media, game art, augmented reality, bio art, public interventions, open source and community-based practices.

Examples of a One-day Event/Activity: conversation, roundtable discussion, or performance.

We seek propositions inspired by (but not limited to) feminism, critical race studies, cyberfeminism, disability and queer studies.

Submissions will be accepted in either English or French.

Studio XX welcomes project proposals from self-identified women, trans, and/or gender fluid artists, curators, activists, collectives, and organizations.


&nbsp;

WHAT WE OFFER

Studio XX offers artist fees based on the CQAM grid.

Selected projects receive artistic and technical support (to be defined according to each project and available resources).

